Categories of Exceptions
<!-- Checked Exceptions – Errors detected at compile-time (e.g., IOException, SQLException).

Unchecked Exceptions (Runtime Exceptions) – Errors detected at runtime (e.g., NullPointerException, ArithmeticException).

Errors – Serious problems that should not be handled (e.g., StackOverflowError, OutOfMemoryError). -->

1 - try-catch Block

try{
    <!-- The code that might throw an exception ! -->
}
catch(ExceptionType e){
    <!-- Handle the exception ! -->
}

2 - finally block 

try{
    <!-- Risky Code -->
}
catch(ExceptionType e){
    <!-- Handle the exception ! -->
}
finalyy{
    <!-- Always Executed ! -->
}

3 - throw keyword 

throw new ExceptionType("Error Message");

4 - throws keyword 

void myMethod() throws ExceptionType{
    <!-- Code that might cause the exception ! -->
}